<td style="width:1.0em; padding:0 0 0 0.6em;">&#160;-&#160;</td>
<td style="padding-left:0em;text-align:left;">Disestablished</td>
<td>9th century CE</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2"><b>Today part of</b></td>
<td>India</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Pallavas</b> ruled regions of northern <a href="Tamil_Nadu" title="Tamil Nadu">Tamil Nadu</a> and southern <a href="Andhra_Pradesh" title="Andhra Pradesh">Andhra Pradesh</a> between the 2nd and 9th centuries CE. The Pallavas gained prominence after the eclipse of the <a href="Satavahanas" title="Satavahanas" class="mw-redirect">Satavahana dynasty</a>, whom the Pallavas served as feudatories.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> A number of legends are associated with the origin of the Pallavas.</p>
